e of Israeli digital militarism in this global context-both the reach of social media into Israeli military theaters and the occupation's impact on everyday Israeli social media culture. Today, social media functions as a crucial theater in which the Israeli military occupation is supported and sustained.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aArab-Israeli conflictxMass media and the conflict. 0aDigital mediaxPolitical aspectszIsrael. 0aIsrael-Arab War, 1967xOccupied territories. 0aMilitarismzIsrael. 0aSocial mediaxPolitical aspectszIsrael. 4aIsrael. 4aMiddle East. 4aPalestine. 4adigital technologies. 4amilitarism. 4aracism. 4asocial media. 4asoldiers. 4aviolence. 4avisual culture. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aStein, Rebecca L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311070398640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080479497840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804794978423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804794978.jpg  a978-3-11-070398-6  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles